      "prompt": "Experimenting with prompts that generate different styles of posters for top athletes.\n\nPrompt:\n\n<instruction> Input A is the subject. You are a god-tier poster designer, art director, and print-production specialist. PHASE 1 — AXIS SELECTION: Randomly select TWO Poster Movements (the two ROWS) and TWO Graphic Systems (the two COLUMNS). Poster Movements: [Vintage Boxing Fight Bill, 1972 Olympic Pictogram Modernism, Soviet Sports Constructivism, 1990s Sports-Magazine Grunge, Japanese Baseball Advertising, Art Deco Stadium Poster, Terrace Football Ultras Graphics, Y2K Sneaker Campaign Minimalism] Graphic Systems: [Risograph Halftone, Oversized Stat Typography, Screenprint Misregistration, Torn Ticket Collage, Diagonal Speed-Line Geometry, Duotone Photo Posterization, Chalk-and-Tape Locker-Room Lettering, Neon Scoreboard Layering] PHASE 2 — MATRIX RENDER: ONE single 16:9 image divided into a clean 2x2 grid with thin gutters. Each quadrant is a finished poster equal to the intersection of its row's Movement and its column's System: top-left = M1×S1, top-right = M1×S2, bottom-left = M2×S1, bottom-right = M2×S2. INVARIANTS (all four panels): the subject's exact pose, silhouette, and spatial composition from Input A must remain recognizable. Only surface treatment, palette, typography, and texture may change. </instruction>",
      "prompt_ko": "입력된 인물 사진(Input A)을 기반으로, 8가지 '포스터 무브먼트'(빈티지 복싱빌·72올림픽 픽토그램 모더니즘·소비에트 스포츠 구성주의·90s 스포츠매거진 그런지·일본 야구광고·아르데코 스타디움·테라스 훌리건 그래픽·Y2K 스니커 미니멀리즘) 중 2개와 8가지 '그래픽 시스템'(리소그래프 하프톤·초대형 스탯 타이포·스크린프린트 미스레지스트레이션·찢어진 티켓 콜라주·대각선 스피드라인·듀오톤 포스터화·초크앤테이프 락커룸 레터링·네온 스코어보드 레이어링) 중 2개를 랜덤 조합, 16:9 한 장에 2x2 그리드로 4가지 스타일 포스터를 동시 생성. 4패널 모두 원본 인물의 포즈·실루엣·공간구성은 그대로 유지하고 표면처리/팔레트/타이포/질감만 바뀜. 레퍼런스 사진(Input A) 기반 시스템 프롬프트라 원본 그대로는 실행 불가 — gen_prompt는 가상의 농구선수 점프슛 포즈를 인라인으로 묘사해 대체.",
      "gen_prompt": "Create ONE single 16:9 image divided into a clean 2x2 grid with thin gutters. The subject in all four panels is the same professional basketball player, mid-air in a dramatic jump-shot pose, arm fully extended, ball just leaving the fingertips, body in a sharp diagonal silhouette against a plain backdrop — this exact pose, silhouette, and spatial composition must stay identical and recognizable across all four panels. Each quadrant reimagines the same pose in a different poster style: TOP-LEFT = Vintage Boxing Fight Bill crossed with Risograph Halftone (aged cream paper, bold woodblock-style type, coarse halftone dot texture, warm sepia and red ink). TOP-RIGHT = Vintage Boxing Fight Bill crossed with Oversized Stat Typography (the same aged fight-bill layout but dominated by giant bold numeral stats overlapping the figure). BOTTOM-LEFT = 1990s Sports-Magazine Grunge crossed with Risograph Halftone (torn distressed textures, grungy magazine collage elements, combined with coarse halftone dot grain and fluorescent riso ink colors). BOTTOM-RIGHT = 1990s Sports-Magazine Grunge crossed with Oversized Stat Typography (grunge magazine texture with huge bold stat-number typography slashing across the figure). Only surface treatment, color palette, typography, and texture differ between panels — the pose and composition remain constant. Sharp print-production quality, clean thin white gutters separating the four panels, no watermark, no real athlete likeness or real team branding.",
