      "prompt": "Haven't done this map prompts for a while. This one is your standard JSON format\n\n2x2 grid, 16:9, do this for 4 famous cities: {\n  \"input\": {\n    \"place\": \"[any_city_region_or_location]\",\n    \"map_context\": \"[optional]\",\n    \"style_context\": \"[optional]\"\n  },\n  \"hardcoding\": false,\n  \"task\": \"generate a realistic geographic pop-up map diorama.\",\n  \"place_identity\": {\n    \"name\": \"infer_or_use_input_place\",\n    \"map_position\": \"infer_correct_geographic_location\",\n    \"regional_context\": \"infer_country_region_coast_river_or_terrain\",\n    \"urban_character\": \"infer_architecture_density_and_layout\"\n  },\n  \"miniature_city\": {\n    \"landmarks\": \"infer_recognizable_place_specific_structures\",\n    \"skyline\": \"build_from_actual_place_dna\",\n    \"waterways\": \"infer_rivers_bays_canals_harbors_or_none\",\n    \"bridges\": \"infer_only_if_geographically_relevant\",\n    \"parks_and_roads\": \"infer_local_urban_texture\",\n    \"scale\": \"miniature_architectural_model\"\n  },\n  \"map_surface\": {\n    \"style\": \"infer_atlas_vintage_nautical_transit_historical_or_fantasy_map\",\n    \"labels\": \"generate_contextual_map_labels\",\n    \"paper\": \"fibrous_printed_material_with_thickness\",\n    \"tear\": \"irregular_ripped_opening_around_place\",\n    \"edge_behavior\": \"curled_fibers_cast_shadows\"\n  },\n  \"rendering\": {\n    \"camera\": \"macro_product_photography\",\n    \"lighting\": \"soft_studio_or_natural_editorial\",\n    \"depth\": \"shallow_depth_of_field\",\n    \"label\": \"3d_place_name_inferred_from_input\",\n    \"quality\": \"realistic_miniature_diorama\"\n  },\n  \"negative_rules\": [\n    \"no hard-coded city\",\n    \"no wrong landmarks\",\n    \"no inaccurate geography\",\n    \"no random skyline\",\n    \"no flat paper hole\",\n    \"no unrelated bridges\",\n    \"no copied map labels\",\n    \"no generic tourist collage\"\n  ]\n}",
      "prompt_ko": "[place] 하나만 바꾸면 어떤 도시/지역이든 지도 위 찢어진 구멍에서 미니어처 건축 디오라마가 튀어나오는 장면을 만드는 JSON 스키마 템플릿. hardcoding:false로 명시해 AI가 실제 지리(위치·해안/강/지형)와 랜드마크를 스스로 추론하도록 강제. 지도 표면은 아틀라스/빈티지/항해용/교통/역사/판타지 지도 중 문맥에 맞게 추론, 섬유질 인쇄물 질감+불규칙한 찢김+말린 가장자리 그림자. 매크로 제품사진 카메라+얕은 심도+3D 장소명 라벨. negative_rules로 하드코딩된 도시·틀린 랜드마크·부정확한 지리·무작위 스카이라인·평평한 종이구멍·무관한 다리·복사된 지도라벨·일반적 관광콜라주를 명시적으로 금지 — gdgtify-folded-map(지도가 건축으로 접히는 컨셉)과는 다른, '지도에 뚫린 구멍에서 튀어나온 디오라마' 컨셉.",
      "gen_prompt": "2x2 grid, 16:9, do this for 4 famous cities. For each: input place = Venice, Italy. Task: generate a realistic geographic pop-up map diorama. Infer the correct geographic location, regional context (coastal lagoon city, canals, Adriatic Sea), and urban character (dense low-rise stone architecture, narrow alleys). Build a miniature architectural-model city rising out of the map with recognizable landmarks (St. Mark's Campanile, Rialto Bridge, domed basilica), a skyline built from Venice's actual urban DNA, canals and waterways, bridges only where geographically relevant, and locally accurate urban texture. The map surface is a vintage nautical chart style with contextual map labels, printed on fibrous paper with visible thickness, torn open with an irregular ripped opening around the miniature city, curled paper fibers casting shadows at the torn edge. Rendered as macro product photography, soft studio lighting, shallow depth of field, a small 3D place-name label reading 'VENICE', realistic miniature diorama quality. Avoid: hard-coded generic city, wrong landmarks, inaccurate geography, random skyline, a flat paper hole with no depth, unrelated bridges, copied map labels, generic tourist collage.",
