      "title": "수량 비교 포스터 — 물성화된 스케일 갭 (화이트 배경, 셔틀 예제)",
      "prompt": "INPUT = {     \"question\": \"[COMPARISON_QUESTION]\",     \"entity_a\": \"[ENTITY_A]\",     \"entity_b\": \"[ENTITY_B]\",     \"values\": \"[SUPPLIED_OR_VERIFIED_VALUES]\",     \"visual_tone\": \"[VISUAL_TONE]\" }  class DataCheck:     def validate(self):         return {             \"entity_a_value\": \"use supplied or verified range only\",             \"entity_b_value\": \"use supplied or verified range only\",             \"unit\": \"same unit or clearly comparable unit\",             \"gap\": \"show multiplier or order-of-magnitude gap only if data supports it\",             \"source\": \"include concise source line\"         }  class QuantityObject:     def build(self, entity, value):         return {             \"container\": AI_INFER(entity, \"jar, bottle, case, room, stadium, shelf, grid, box, pile, field, vault\"),             \"material\": AI_INFER(entity, \"recognizable particle or object texture\"),             \"scale\": \"physically staged to make the quantity emotionally legible\",             \"label\": \"short museum-style label with value range\"         }  class PosterSystem:     def compose(self):         return {             \"headline\": INPUT[\"question\"],             \"answer_line\": \"one clear statement of which is larger and by how much\",             \"hero_comparison\": \"two objects staged side by side\",             \"scale_bar\": \"bottom order-of-magnitude ruler\",             \"mood\": INPUT[\"visual_tone\"]         }  def render():     \"\"\"     Generate a mindblowing numerosity comparison poster.     Make two abstract quantities feel physically present.     The viewer should understand the scale gap before reading the fine print.     Use only supplied or verified numbers.     \"\"\"",
      "prompt_ko": "바이럴 수량비교 비주얼의 함수형 템플릿. 구조 = DataCheck(공급/검증된 수치만·동일단위·갭은 데이터가 지지할 때만·출처 한 줄) + QuantityObject(엔티티를 병·케이스·경기장·그리드 등 물리 용기에 스테이징, 뮤지엄 라벨) + PosterSystem(질문 헤드라인·명확한 답 한 줄·나란한 히어로 비교·하단 자릿수 눈금자). '추상적 수량 두 개를 물리적으로 느끼게' 하는 게 목적. ★제이크 지시: 화이트 배경으로 재현.",
      "gen_prompt": "A mindblowing numerosity comparison poster on a clean pure white background, museum-exhibit lighting. Headline question in bold editorial type at top: “HOW MANY BUSES DOES 100,000 PEOPLE TAKE?”. Answer line beneath in one clear statement: “2,223 forty-five-seat shuttle buses — enough to line up for 27 kilometers.” Hero comparison staged side by side as physically present objects: on the left, a vast dense crowd of 100,000 tiny detailed human figures packed into a glass stadium-shaped container; on the right, a long orderly grid formation of 2,223 miniature white-and-red shuttle buses arranged in neat rows on a white field, each bus casting a soft shadow. Both quantities feel tangible and countable, staged like museum dioramas with short museum-style labels: “ATTENDEES — 100,000” and “SHUTTLE BUSES — 2,223 UNITS”. At the bottom, an order-of-magnitude scale bar ruler from 10 to 100,000. Concise source line in small type: “45 seats per bus, single trip”. Clean white minimal visual tone, photorealistic miniature detail, soft even light, premium data-journalism poster.",
      "result": "results/gdgtify-quantity-compare.png",
      "seed": 851790726
