      "prompt": "Design a refined minimalist travel poster in a sophisticated editorial flat-vector style, drawing inspiration from contemporary Japanese travel illustrations and high-end tourism publications.\n\nScene:\nIllustrate a breathtaking panoramic landscape of [CITY NAME], showcasing its most recognizable landmarks, scenic waterfront, mountain ranges, gardens, skyline, and beloved local attractions. Populate the scene with casually dressed travelers enjoying the destination—strolling through parks, relaxing on benches with coffee, photographing the scenery, sketching, cycling along pathways, or watching boats glide across the water. The overall mood should be tranquil, welcoming, and effortlessly elegant.\n\nArt Style:\n\n- Modern flat-vector artwork with delicate hand-drawn line accents\n- Muted pastel palette featuring warm cream, soft blue, sage green, sandy beige, and gentle terracotta\n- Scandinavian simplicity blended with contemporary Japanese editorial design\n- Minimal geometric forms enhanced with subtle gradients\n- Refined architectural details and thoughtfully illustrated landmarks\n- Soft atmospheric depth for a natural sense of distance\n- Spacious, uncluttered composition with generous negative space\n\nTypography:\nPosition a large, sophisticated serif title featuring the city name at the top of the poster, accompanied by a smaller, understated subtitle below. Incorporate tasteful local visual details such as directional signs, café names, transit signage, or other subtle location-specific typography that complements the city's character. The text should feel luxurious, timeless, and editorial.\n\nComposition:\nVertical A4 layout with a balanced foreground, middle ground, and background, creating strong visual depth. Include reflective water, lush trees, seasonal flowers, mountain silhouettes, and everyday visitors interacting naturally with the environment to evoke a calm, inspiring travel experience.\n\nQuality:\nExceptional editorial-quality vector illustration with crisp, precise linework, soft natural lighting, premium tourism campaign aesthetics, Behance-worthy presentation, Pinterest-inspired styling, Apple-like minimalist refinement, highly detailed execution, and stunning 8K resolution.",
      "prompt_ko": "[CITY NAME]의 파노라마를 일본 에디토리얼 × 스칸디나비안 플랫벡터로 그리는 정제된 여행 포스터. 랜드마크·수변·산·정원·스카이라인 + 여행자들(산책·벤치 커피·촬영·스케치·자전거). 뮤트 파스텔(웜크림·소프트블루·세이지·테라코타), 섬세한 손그림 라인 액센트, 넉넉한 여백, 대형 세리프 도시명 타이포.",
      "gen_prompt": "Design a refined minimalist travel poster in a sophisticated editorial flat-vector style, drawing inspiration from contemporary Japanese travel illustrations and high-end tourism publications.\n\nScene:\nIllustrate a breathtaking panoramic landscape of Gangneung, a serene coastal city in Korea — Gyeongpo Lake pavilion, pine-lined Anmok beach coffee street, Ojukheon hanok, distant Taebaek mountain ridges, a slow sea-side rail line, showcasing its most recognizable landmarks, scenic waterfront, mountain ranges, gardens, skyline, and beloved local attractions. Populate the scene with casually dressed travelers enjoying the destination—strolling through parks, relaxing on benches with coffee, photographing the scenery, sketching, cycling along pathways, or watching boats glide across the water. The overall mood should be tranquil, welcoming, and effortlessly elegant.\n\nArt Style:\n\n- Modern flat-vector artwork with delicate hand-drawn line accents\n- Muted pastel palette featuring warm cream, soft blue, sage green, sandy beige, and gentle terracotta\n- Scandinavian simplicity blended with contemporary Japanese editorial design\n- Minimal geometric forms enhanced with subtle gradients\n- Refined architectural details and thoughtfully illustrated landmarks\n- Soft atmospheric depth for a natural sense of distance\n- Spacious, uncluttered composition with generous negative space\n\nTypography:\nPosition a large, sophisticated serif title featuring the city name at the top of the poster, accompanied by a smaller, understated subtitle below. Incorporate tasteful local visual details such as directional signs, café names, transit signage, or other subtle location-specific typography that complements the city's character. The text should feel luxurious, timeless, and editorial.\n\nComposition:\nVertical A4 layout with a balanced foreground, middle ground, and background, creating strong visual depth. Include reflective water, lush trees, seasonal flowers, mountain silhouettes, and everyday visitors interacting naturally with the environment to evoke a calm, inspiring travel experience.\n\nQuality:\nExceptional editorial-quality vector illustration with crisp, precise linework, soft natural lighting, premium tourism campaign aesthetics, Behance-worthy presentation, Pinterest-inspired styling, Apple-like minimalist refinement, highly detailed execution, and stunning 8K resolution.\n\nThe large serif title reads “GANGNEUNG” with a small subtitle “EAST SEA · COFFEE · PINE WIND”.",
