      "prompt": "2x2 grid, 16:9, do this for iPhone, CyberTruck and 2 other popular gadgets: A top-down flat-lay where [$gadgets' parts and elements] are pinned at their true geographic origins (where they are sourced) with no map drawn beneath them, placement density matching real-world distribution, so the objects alone assemble the recognizable outline of [REGION/WORLD] as the silhouette ::5 Origin Logic: AI_INFER 30–60 themed objects and place each at its authentic home location — clustered where origins genuinely cluster, absent where the theme is absent, coastlines and borders implied purely by where objects stop — geography emerging from provenance alone ::5 Composition: Map-true placement without any drawn basemap, honest density variation, edges defined only by object boundaries, clean regional silhouette, generous margin ::3 Material Physics: Real themed objects with regionally accurate variants and materials, consistent matte finish, soft shadows ::2 Illumination: Flat overhead softbox, no glare ::2 Typography: Tiny origin-place labels beside key clusters ::2 Render Stack: Origin-atlas flat-lay, provenance-map arrangement, geography-from-objects chart, 8k ::1 Negative: [drawn map or borders underneath, geographically wrong placement, uniform even scatter, unrecognizable region, broken silhouette, tilt, hands] ::-1",
      "prompt_ko": "가젯 부품들을 실제 원산지 좌표에 핀 — **바탕지도 없이** 오브젝트 배치 밀도만으로 지역/세계 실루엣이 떠오르게 하는 공급망 시각화. Origin Logic: 30~60개 부품을 진짜 산지에 배치(산지가 몰리는 곳은 클러스터, 없는 곳은 공백, 해안선·국경은 오브젝트가 멈추는 자리로만 암시) — '지리가 원산지에서 창발'. 데이터 피지케이션 시리즈의 공급망 편. 작성자도 '로직 더 다듬어야' 단서.",
