      "prompt": "input_topic ::= \"<insert movie / game / manga / franchise here>\"\n\n[topic_analysis]\nfrom input_topic, infer and assign:\n- structure: the most iconic multi-space location (base, ship, tower, household, hq).\n- rooms: 3–4 distinct zones inside, each with its own function and palette.\n- residents: 5–7 characters distributed across rooms, each mid-action and appropriate to its zone.\n- easter_eggs: 10+ recognizable props, signage, and a deep_cut detail hidden in one room.\n- light_logic: how each zone is lit differently (screen glow, warm lamp, daylight slot).\n\n<scene> ::= <shell> \"+\" <room_grid> \"+\" <residents> \"+\" <dense_dressing> \"+\" <render_env>\n\n<shell> ::= \"a single isometric building-block of structure with two adjoining walls and the roof\n             cut away on a clean section line, floating in a plain neutral void, true architecture and materials\"\n\n<room_grid> ::= \"rooms stacked and adjacent inside the shell — each a fully realized tiny space with\n                 its own [light_logic], floor, and furniture, separated by visible interior walls and stairs\"\n\n<residents> ::= \"residents placed one-to-two per room, each genuinely doing something tied to that\n                 zone (cooking, repairing, monitoring, resting), correctly scaled to the furniture;\n                 two of them interacting across a doorway\"\n\n<dense_dressing> ::= \"easter_eggs distributed by room — props, posters, gear, clutter that is full but\n                      readable — with the deep_cut detail tucked into one corner for fans to find\"\n\n<render_env> ::= \"clean 3d render, soft global illumination plus the per-room practical lights, gentle\n                  ambient occlusion in the corners, true isometric 45° camera, neutral seamless backdrop, crisp throughout\"\n\n[instruction]\nrender one image of <scene>, deriving structure, rooms, residents, and easter_eggs from input_topic.\ndensity is zoned: each room reads on its own, residents act, lighting differs per space. miniature isometric cutaway.",
      "prompt_ko": "BNF 문법 형식 템플릿. [프랜차이즈]에서 상징적 다공간 구조물(기지/배/타워/저택)을 추론 → 벽 2면+지붕을 절단선으로 잘라낸 아이소메트릭 단면 + 존별 조명 로직이 다른 방 3~4개 + 방마다 기능에 맞는 행동 중인 주민 5~7명(문간 너머 상호작용 2명 포함) + 이스터에그 소품 10+와 딥컷 디테일 1개. 중립 보이드에 부유.",
      "gen_prompt": "A single isometric building-block of a busy Korean jjimjilbang (bathhouse-sauna complex) with two adjoining walls and the roof cut away on a clean section line, floating in a plain neutral warm-gray void, true architecture and materials. Inside, four stacked and adjacent fully-realized tiny rooms, each with its own light logic, floor and furniture, separated by visible interior walls and stairs: 1) a steamy hot-bath hall with pale teal tiles lit by cool skylight shafts; 2) a warm ochre kiln sauna room glowing amber from its stone dome; 3) a cozy snack lounge lit by a humming refrigerator and TV screen glow, with sikhye drinks and baked eggs on trays; 4) a dim nap room with bunk mats and one warm floor lamp. Six tiny residents mid-action, correctly scaled to furniture: a woman pouring water in the bath hall, a man wiping sweat in the kiln, two friends in sheep-horn towel hats chatting across the lounge doorway while sharing snacks, a sleeper curled in the nap room, an attendant restocking towels on the stairs. Dense recognizable dressing by room: stacked yellow towels, wooden pillows, a scale, lockers, hanging back-scrubbers, a retro fan, slippers lined at thresholds, an old wall clock, a hand-written menu board — and one deep-cut detail: a tiny lost single sock behind the lounge fridge. Crisp miniature scale, tactile materials, softly rendered, architectural cutaway precision.",
