      "prompt": "2x2 grid, 16:9, 4 mind-bending science facts input = [subject / fact_or_stat / reference_medium / data_mode] run science_fact_visualization_extraction: subject_dna := infer what subject is, its scale, material, shape, and recognizable visual identity fact_type := infer whether the fact is density, size, mass, speed, heat, pressure, distance, probability, lifespan, energy, scarcity, cost, or another measurable category measured_value := use provided value or verified value; if illustrative, clearly mark as illustrative reference_comparison := infer what the value is being compared against visual_metaphor := infer the most intuitive physical demonstration of the fact environment := infer scene that makes the comparison visible physical_interaction := infer floating, sinking, stretching, melting, compressing, orbiting, stacking, shrinking, overflowing, balancing, glowing, freezing, or other behavior callout_text := generate concise explanatory label leader_line := connect label to the exact visual evidence camera := infer cinematic educational framing lighting := infer clean, beautiful, credible science-documentary lighting render: a cinematic visual explanation where the fact is embodied by the subject's interaction with the reference medium. forbidden: hard-coded planet, hard-coded water, hard-coded density value, hard-coded text box, unsupported physics, fake precision without data, purely decorative infographic text.",
      "prompt_ko": "과학적으로 놀라운 사실 4개를 2x2 그리드로 시각화하는 함수형 템플릿. 하드코딩된 예시(행성·물·밀도값) 없이 subject·fact_type·비교대상·시각적 은유를 매번 새로 추론하도록 설계돼, 밀도·크기·질량·속도·열·압력 등 측정 가능한 카테고리 아무거나 넣어서 재사용 가능. Krea2용으로는 원본의 의사코드 필드 구조(subject_dna, fact_type, visual_metaphor 등)를 실제 사실 4개(중성자별 밀도·꿀의 보존력·번개의 온도·태양빛 도달시간)로 구체화해 자연어 묘사로 풀어씀.",
      "gen_prompt": "A cinematic 2x2 grid infographic, 16:9 widescreen, each of the four panels visually explaining one mind-bending science fact through a physical demonstration rather than decorative charts. Panel 1 (density): a single ordinary teaspoon sinking straight through solid ground under its own weight, a deep crater forming beneath it, with a clean callout label and thin leader line reading 'a teaspoon of neutron star material weighs about 5.5 billion tons' — a small silhouette of a mountain placed beside it for scale comparison. Panel 2 (preservation): a sealed clay jar of golden honey resting undisturbed inside a sunlit ancient Egyptian tomb chamber, faint dust and millennia-old artifacts around it, callout label reading 'honey found in 3,000-year-old tombs is still edible' with a leader line pointing to the jar. Panel 3 (heat): a jagged bolt of lightning striking downward beside a small glowing sphere representing the Sun's surface, the lightning rendered visibly brighter and hotter than the sun sphere, callout label 'a lightning bolt is roughly five times hotter than the Sun's surface' with a leader line connecting both elements. Panel 4 (distance/time): Earth and the Sun connected by a glowing beam of light with a subtle motion trail, a small clock overlay showing an eight-minute delay, callout label 'the sunlight reaching you is already eight minutes old' with a leader line to the clock. Each panel rendered with clean, credible science-documentary lighting, realistic materials and textures, a dark neutral background separating the panels with a thin hairline grid, minimal sans-serif callout typography, no decorative charts or fake precision — purely physical visual demonstration of each fact.",
