      "title": "사무용품으로 지은 도시 스카이라인 — 2x2 함수형 템플릿",
      "prompt": "2x2 grid, 16:9, 4 AI inferred topics <instructions> Input = Office Supply Category. Identify 4 distinct desk supplies (e.g., Paperclips, Sticky Notes, Fountain Pens, Rubber Bands). Function Draw ($ Office_Supply, $ Iconic_City_Skyline) ... Anchor: [$Iconic_City_Skyline] :: [$Office_Supply]::4 | Morphology: The monumental architecture of [$Iconic_City_Skyline] meticulously erected via the complex assemblage and stacking of [$Office_Supply]. Skyscrapers and bridges engineered from the constituent shapes of the stationery. | Material Physics: The specific tensile strength, metallic wire bending, or matte paper texture of [$Office_Supply] defining the structural integrity of the city. Macro-photography revealing the mundane materials... </instructions>",
      "prompt_ko": "사무용품으로 상징적 도시 스카이라인을 짓는 2x2 그리드(16:9) 함수형 템플릿. 입력=사무용품 카테고리 → 서로 다른 책상용품 4종을 모델이 스스로 추론(예: 클립·포스트잇·만년필·고무줄) → `Draw($Office_Supply, $Iconic_City_Skyline)`. **Morphology**: 해당 도시의 기념비적 건축을 그 사무용품의 복잡한 조립·적층으로 정교하게 세운다 — 마천루와 교량이 문구류의 구성 형태로 공학적으로 구축됨. **Material Physics**: 그 사무용품 고유의 인장강도·금속 와이어의 굽힘·무광 종이 질감이 도시의 구조적 무결성을 규정한다. 매크로 촬영으로 평범한 재료를 드러낸다. ※원문에 `...` 생략이 포함돼 있어(작성자 본인의 축약) 그 범위까지만 확보.",
      "gen_prompt": "A 2x2 grid, 16:9 widescreen, of four macro photographs in which iconic city skylines are meticulously constructed from ordinary desk supplies, each panel a different supply and a different city, consistent lighting and camera height, clean neutral studio backdrop. Top-left: the Manhattan skyline erected entirely from bent silver paperclips — skyscrapers and suspension bridges engineered from looping wire forms, the tensile springiness of the metal defining the structural logic, macro focus revealing brushed steel and tiny scratches. Top-right: the Tokyo skyline built from stacked and folded sticky notes — towers assembled from layered yellow, pink and mint squares, matte paper fibre texture and slightly curling adhesive edges giving the buildings their mass. Bottom-left: the Dubai skyline constructed from fountain pens standing and interlocked — lacquered barrels and polished nibs forming tapering spires, glossy resin and gold trim catching the light. Bottom-right: the London skyline formed from stretched and knotted rubber bands — bridges and domes suspended in taut elastic curves, the matte rubber stretch and tension defining the structure. Macro photography revealing the mundane materials up close, thin clean dividing lines between panels, honest material physics throughout.",
      "result": "results/gdgtify-office-supply-city-skyline-grid.png",
