      "prompt": "Act as the Global Creative Director for Royal Enfield. Think like a collaboration between Royal Enfield Global Design, Sid Lee, AKQA, Wieden+Kennedy, Pentagram, National Geographic Adventure, Fuel Motorcycles, The Ride Magazine, and Apple Marketing. Your objective is NOT to create a motorcycle wallpaper. Your objective is to create a flagship Instagram campaign that celebrates instinct, freedom and exploration. The final artwork should feel like a frame from a premium adventure documentary rather than a motorcycle advertisement. Reject: generic bike posters, floating motorcycles, cheap CGI, artificial dust, oversaturated colours, AI-generated automotive clichés. Campaign: IN GUT WE TRUST. Platform: Instagram. Aspect Ratio: 4:5 Vertical. Resolution: 8K Ultra High Resolution. Hyper-realistic Commercial Photography. Editorial Adventure Advertising. Brand: Royal Enfield. Motorcycle: Bear 650. Category: Modern Retro Scrambler. Core Values: Freedom, Adventure, Exploration, Authenticity, Craftsmanship, Instinct, Heritage. Brand Truth: The Bear 650 isn't built to race. It is built to explore roads that don't appear on maps. Psychological Position: Ride because your instinct says yes. Hero Motorcycle: Royal Enfield Bear 650. Exact factory specification. Maintain original geometry. Correct suspension height. Original spoke wheels. OEM tyres. Original exhaust. Correct engine detailing. Original fuel tank graphics. Maintain exact paint finish. Recommended colour: Wild Honey OR Golden Shadow. Maintain authentic Royal Enfield craftsmanship. Location: Remote mountain trail during golden hour. Rocky terrain. Dry grass. Ancient winding road. Distant mountain ranges. Warm dusty atmosphere. No modern buildings. No traffic. No city. Only endless landscape. The environment should communicate adventure before the motorcycle does. Story: The rider has just stopped after discovering a breathtaking viewpoint. Helmet rests naturally on the handlebar. Fine dust still hangs in the air. Engine quietly ticks as it cools. The landscape is silent. The Bear 650 stands ready for the next unknown road. This is not about speed. This is about freedom. Composition: Top: Royal Enfield logo. Small and understated. Large editorial headline. IN GUT. WE TRUST. Center: Motorcycle occupies approximately 70% of the frame. Three-quarter front angle. Low camera position. Strong leading lines. Natural depth. Bottom: Minimal specification panel. 648cc Parallel Twin. 47 PS. Scrambler DNA. Ride Beyond Roads. Small CTA. Explore More. Swiss editorial grid. Large negative space. Perfect visual hierarchy. Graphic Design: Minimal expedition-inspired graphics. Swiss Grid. Topographic contour lines. GPS coordinates. Altitude marker. Compass bearing. Subtle trail route overlay. Tiny technical annotations. Everything inspired by adventure maps. No decorative clutter. Colour System: Primary: Wild Honey Yellow, Matte Black, Warm Sand, Stone Grey. Secondary: Burnt Earth, Graphite, Steel, Warm Beige. Accent: Brushed Aluminium, Royal Enfield Red (very subtle), Dusty Olive. Lighting: Golden hour. Natural low-angle sunlight. Soft volumetric haze. Long shadows. Warm rim light. Realistic chrome reflections. Premium commercial motorcycle lighting. Natural HDR. Camera: Phase One XF IQ4 150MP. Schneider Kreuznach 80mm LS. Medium-format photography. Low eye-level perspective. Ultra-high dynamic range. True-to-life proportions. Natural depth of field. No exaggerated wide-angle distortion. Material Detail: Metallic paint texture. Brushed aluminium. Engine cooling fins. Tyre sidewall texture. Fine dust on swingarm. Natural chain finish. Leather seat grain. Brake rotor machining marks. Spoke reflections. Stone texture. Everything physically accurate. Colour Grading: Kodak Vision3 250D inspired. Warm amber highlights. Deep matte blacks. Earth-tone saturation. Soft cinematic contrast. Natural skin of the landscape. Fine analogue grain. Luxury adventure colour science.\n\nNegative Prompt: NO racing posture. NO track environment. NO neon lighting. NO futuristic city. NO excessive mud splash. NO drifting. NO burnout. NO fake motion blur. NO oversized typography. NO AI artifacts. NO plastic textures. NO unrealistic reflections. NO clutter. Quality Bar: Royal Enfield Global Campaign. National Geographic Adventure. Apple-level composition. Behance Featured. Cannes Lions Automotive. Premium editorial storytelling. Viewer reaction: This isn't a motorcycle advertisement. It's an invitation to disappear into the horizon.",
      "prompt_ko": "raw Royal Enfield Bear 650 사진을 업로드해 하이엔드 어드벤처 캠페인 포스터로 변환하는 함수형 디렉터 프롬프트. 'Global Creative Director for Royal Enfield' 페르소나로, 오토바이 광고가 아닌 프리미엄 어드벤처 다큐 프레임을 목표. 캠페인='IN GUT WE TRUST', 인스타 4:5 세로, 8K 하이퍼리얼 상업사진. 골든아워 산악 트레일, Bear 650 팩토리 스펙 유지(지오메트리·스포크휠·Wild Honey 컬러), Swiss 에디토리얼 그리드 — 상단 로고+대형 헤드라인 / 중앙 오토바이 70% / 하단 스펙패널(648cc·47PS·Scrambler DNA)+CTA, 탐험지도풍 그래픽(등고선·GPS좌표·고도마커·나침반·트레일 오버레이), 컬러시스템(Wild Honey Yellow/Matte Black/Warm Sand/Stone Grey 등), 골든아워 볼류메트릭 조명, Phase One 중형카메라, Kodak Vision3 250D 컬러그레이딩. ★참조 이미지(오토바이) 업로드가 전제인 형태지만 캠페인 구성·Swiss그리드·스펙패널·컬러시스템·어드벤처 지도 그래픽 요소가 재사용 가치. 네거티브 프롬프트 및 퀄리티 바 포함.",
      "gen_prompt": "Premium adventure documentary campaign poster, hyper-realistic commercial photography, 4:5 vertical editorial layout. A modern retro scrambler motorcycle (honey-yellow / golden fuel tank, matte black frame, spoke wheels, twin exhaust, engine cooling fins) stands on a remote rocky mountain trail during golden hour, dry grass, ancient winding road, distant mountain ranges, warm dusty haze, no buildings, no city, endless landscape. A helmet rests on the handlebar, fine dust hanging in the air. Composition: small understated logo mark top-left, large editorial headline 'IN GUT WE TRUST' top, motorcycle occupies ~70% of the frame at three-quarter front angle from a low camera position, bottom minimal specification panel (648cc Parallel Twin, 47 PS, Scrambler DNA) with a small 'Explore More' CTA. Swiss editorial grid, large negative space, perfect visual hierarchy. Expedition-inspired graphic overlays: topographic contour lines, GPS coordinates, altitude marker, compass bearing, subtle trail-route line, tiny technical annotations, adventure-map aesthetic, no clutter. Colour system: wild honey yellow, matte black, warm sand, stone grey, brushed aluminium accents. Golden-hour natural low-angle sunlight, soft volumetric haze, long shadows, warm rim light, realistic chrome reflections. Medium-format look, ultra-high dynamic range, natural depth of field, no wide-angle distortion. Material detail: metallic paint texture, brushed aluminium, tyre sidewall grain, fine dust on swingarm, leather seat grain, spoke reflections, stone texture. Colour grading inspired by Kodak Vision3 250D: warm amber highlights, deep matte blacks, earth-tone saturation, soft cinematic contrast, fine analogue grain, luxury adventure colour science.",
