      "title": "데일리 무드 콜라주 다이어리 포스터 템플릿 (9:16 찢은종이 에디토리얼)",
      "prompt": "Create a 9:16 vertical editorial collage poster.\n\nTheme: [THEME]\nSeries title: [TITLE]\nSubtitle: [SUBTITLE]\nMain subject: [PERSON / PRODUCT / SCENE]\nSetting: [CITY STREET / COAST / FLOWER SHOP / CAFÉ / OTHER]\nMain colors: [COLOR 1] + [COLOR 2]\nAccent color: [ACCENT COLOR]\nSmall text elements: [TIME / LOCATION / ISSUE NUMBER / SHORT PHRASES]\n\nUse a warm off-white paper background with generous negative space. Place one realistic full-body subject as the main visual anchor, occupying around 60–70% of the poster height. The subject should feel natural and alive, with realistic skin, hair, clothing texture, body proportions, and a relaxed everyday action rather than a stiff fashion pose.\n\nBuild the composition with layered torn-paper photography, grayscale environment fragments, receipts, tickets, handwritten notes, small labels, stamps, paper tape, and 1–2 bold geometric color blocks. Keep all supporting elements secondary to the main subject.\n\nUse a balanced mix of large editorial typography, small typewriter-style labels, and a few handwritten lines. The text should feel original and connected to the theme, not copied from any reference image.\n\nThe overall look should feel like an independent magazine page, visual diary, travel journal, or lifestyle moodboard: nostalgic, clean, tactile, slightly imperfect, and carefully composed.\n\nKeep the visual hierarchy clear:\n1. Main title\n2. Full-body subject\n3. Large color shape\n4. Grayscale scene fragments\n5. Small notes and labels\n\nAvoid overcrowding, excessive text, repeated layouts, copied phrases, plastic-looking skin, distorted hands, unrealistic clothing, messy collage placement, cheap sticker aesthetics, and unreadable typography.",
      "prompt_ko": "9:16 세로 에디토리얼 콜라주 포스터 함수형 템플릿(MrLarus 'Daily Mood Collage'). 플레이스홀더 = [테마]·[시리즈 타이틀]·[서브타이틀]·[메인 피사체(인물/제품/장면)]·[배경(도시거리/해안/꽃집/카페 등)]·[메인 컬러 2]·[액센트 컬러]·[소형 텍스트(시간/장소/이슈번호/짧은 문구)]. 따뜻한 오프화이트 종이 배경 + 넉넉한 여백, 실사 풀바디 피사체 1명을 포스터 높이 60~70% 차지하는 메인 앵커로(뻣뻣한 패션 포즈 아닌 자연스러운 일상 동작). 찢은종이 포토그래피 레이어·그레이스케일 환경 조각·영수증·티켓·손글씨 노트·라벨·스탬프·종이테이프·기하학 컬러블록 1~2개로 구성. 대형 에디토리얼 타이포 + 타자기풍 소형 라벨 + 손글씨 몇 줄 혼합. 독립잡지 페이지·비주얼 다이어리·트래블 저널·라이프스타일 무드보드 느낌(노스탤직·깔끔·촉각적·약간 불완전). 위계=①메인타이틀 ②풀바디 피사체 ③대형 컬러도형 ④그레이스케일 조각 ⑤소형 노트/라벨. 예시 테마 4종(조용한 꽃·소금기 바닷바람·도시 교통·자정 카페)을 한 시리즈로. ★함수형이라 실제 사용 시 대괄호를 구체값으로 치환.",
      "gen_prompt": "Create a 9:16 vertical editorial collage poster. Theme: a quiet midnight cafe moment. Series title: NIGHT NOTES. Subtitle: moments collected after midnight. Main subject: a young woman in a cozy cream knit sweater and jeans, holding a warm coffee cup, relaxed everyday posture. Setting: a dimly lit late-night cafe with warm window light. Main colors: warm off-white and deep charcoal. Accent color: burnt amber.\n\nUse a warm off-white paper background with generous negative space. Place one realistic full-body subject as the main visual anchor, occupying around 60-70% of the poster height. The subject feels natural and alive, with realistic skin, hair, clothing texture, body proportions, and a relaxed everyday action rather than a stiff fashion pose.\n\nBuild the composition with layered torn-paper photography, grayscale environment fragments, receipts, tickets, handwritten notes, small labels, stamps, paper tape, and one bold burnt-amber geometric color block. Keep all supporting elements secondary to the main subject.\n\nUse a balanced mix of large editorial typography reading NIGHT NOTES, small typewriter-style labels reading CAFE and 00:24 and ISSUE 07, and a few handwritten lines. The small text elements read: time 00:24, location downtown cafe, issue number 07, short phrase one more cup.\n\nThe overall look feels like an independent magazine page, visual diary, travel journal, or lifestyle moodboard: nostalgic, clean, tactile, slightly imperfect, and carefully composed. Visual hierarchy: 1 main title, 2 full-body subject, 3 large color shape, 4 grayscale scene fragments, 5 small notes and labels.\n\nAvoid overcrowding, excessive text, plastic-looking skin, distorted hands, unrealistic clothing, messy collage placement, cheap sticker aesthetics, and unreadable typography.",
