      "prompt": "A cute way to visualize 4 fallen empires. \n\nPrompt: \n2x2 grid, 16:9, do this for 4 fallen empires in this style: <transformation>   - Convert the subject into a simplified designer-toy or miniature object with rounded forms, clean surfaces, and charming collectible proportions.   - Reframe the composition as a vintage book-cover or album-poster design with strong silhouette blocks, decorative borders, and aged cream paper space.   - Reinterpret background environments as toy-like diorama scenery, tiny buildings, symbolic props, simplified landscapes, or staged object clusters.   - Replace realistic texture with matte toy material, flat ink print fields, screen-print grain, and subtle paper aging.   - Convert small repeated details into ornamental motifs, stars, gears, clouds, leaves, icons, frame flourishes, or tiny toy props.   - Preserve the subject identity while making it feel like a rare retro cover illustration produced as a boutique designer-toy display.   </transformation>    <layout_rules>   - Use title-zone space without hard-coding specific words.   - Keep the subject readable as both a toy object and a poster icon.   - Use bold silhouettes and large simple color blocks.   - Let decorative borders and ornaments support the subject rather than overpower it.   </layout_rules>    <finish>   - Retro literary cover fused with designer-toy charm.   - Clean, nostalgic, graphic, tactile, and collectible.   - A toy diorama pretending to be a classic printed artifact.   </finish>    <avoid>   - Avoid modern glossy cyberpunk lighting.   - Avoid chaotic sports splatter as the main identity.   - Avoid excessive tiny text.   - Avoid photoreal skin, cloth, or metal.   - Avoid losing the vintage print-poster structure.   </avoid>",
      "prompt_ko": "주제(예시=4개 멸망한 제국)를 디자이너토이+빈티지 북커버로 변환하는 함수형 <transformation> 템플릿(Gdgtify). 2x2 그리드 16:9. 변환=①주제를 둥근 폼·깔끔한 표면·수집형 비율의 단순화 디자이너토이/미니어처 오브젝트로 ②구성을 빈티지 북커버/앨범포스터 디자인으로(강한 실루엣 블록·장식 테두리·낡은 크림 종이 여백) ③배경을 토이 디오라마 씬(작은 건물·상징 소품·단순 풍경)으로 ④질감을 매트 토이 소재·플랫 잉크 프린트·스크린프린트 그레인·미묘한 종이 에이징으로 ⑤작은 반복 디테일을 장식 모티프(별·기어·구름·잎·아이콘·프레임 장식)로 ⑥주제 정체성 유지하며 희귀 레트로 커버 일러스트+부티크 디자이너토이 전시 느낌. 타이틀존 여백(특정 단어 하드코딩 없이). ★역사 주제라 저작권 무관. gen_prompt=로마/이집트/마야/오스만 4제국 데모.",
      "gen_prompt": "A 2x2 grid, 16:9, of four fallen empires, each rendered as a designer-toy vintage book-cover illustration. Panels: 1 the Roman Empire, 2 Ancient Egypt, 3 the Maya civilization, 4 the Ottoman Empire.\nFor each panel: convert the empire's iconic subject into a simplified designer-toy or miniature object with rounded forms, clean surfaces and charming collectible proportions; frame it as a vintage book-cover / album-poster design with strong silhouette blocks, decorative borders and aged cream paper space; reinterpret the background as a toy-like diorama with tiny buildings, symbolic props and simplified landscapes; replace realistic texture with matte toy material, flat ink-print fields, screen-print grain and subtle paper aging; turn small repeated details into ornamental motifs — stars, gears, clouds, leaves, icons and frame flourishes; preserve each empire's identity while making it feel like a rare retro cover illustration produced as a boutique designer-toy display. Reserve a title-zone space in each panel. Cohesive 2x2 grid, warm aged palette.",
      "result": "results/gdgtify-fallen-empires-designertoy-bookcover-grid.png",
      "seed": 549533665,
      "ref_image": null
