      "prompt": "This prompt was mainly for movies but works great for books too. I tried it with GPT but used non-copyrighted books.\n\n2x2 grid, 16:9, do this for 4 public space, non copyrighted scifi books select foreground_environment, hidden_character_silhouette, color_palette from alternative_movie_posters where film = '[franchise]'; /* visual render logic */ -- color_palette: ai_infer(a striking 2-color screen-print palette matching the vibe of [franchise]). -- foreground (positive space): ai_infer(an iconic landscape, forest, or city skyline from the film, drawn in flat vector shapes). -- hidden_character (negative space): ai_infer(the empty sky or shadows between the foreground elements perfectly forming the side-profile of the film's main villain/hero). -- style: minimalist swiss graphic design, flat colors, no gradients, olly moss poster style.",
      "prompt_ko": "영화/책의 대체 포스터를 네거티브 스페이스 실루엣으로 만드는 SQL형 함수형 템플릿(Gdgtify, Olly Moss 스타일). 2x2 그리드 16:9, 4개 작품. select foreground_environment·hidden_character_silhouette·color_palette from alternative_movie_posters where film='[franchise]'. 컬러팔레트=작품 분위기에 맞는 강렬한 2색 스크린프린트. foreground(양성공간)=작품의 아이코닉 풍경·숲·도시 스카이라인을 플랫 벡터로. hidden_character(음성공간)=전경 요소 사이 빈 하늘·그림자가 작품 주인공/빌런의 옆모습 실루엣을 완벽히 형성. 스타일=미니멀 스위스 그래픽 디자인·플랫 컬러·그라디언트 없음·Olly Moss 포스터 스타일. ★[franchise]는 퍼블릭도메인 작품으로 대체(저작권 회피, 원문도 'non-copyrighted books' 지시). gdgtify 기존 장소/통계 컷어웨이와 다른 네거티브 스페이스 실루엣 컨셉.",
      "gen_prompt": "A 2x2 grid, 16:9, of four minimalist Olly-Moss-style negative-space posters for four public-domain science-fiction novels: 1 'The War of the Worlds', 2 'Frankenstein', 3 'Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Sea', 4 'The Time Machine'.\nFor each poster: choose a striking 2-color screen-print palette matching the book's vibe. The foreground (positive space) is an iconic landscape, forest or city skyline from the story drawn in flat vector shapes. The hidden character (negative space) — the empty sky or the shadows between the foreground elements — perfectly forms the side-profile silhouette of the story's main character or menace. Style: minimalist Swiss graphic design, flat colors, no gradients, Olly Moss poster style, clean 2x2 grid, thin gutters between panels.",
