      "prompt": "✨山顶别墅推演设计概念稿Conceptual Design Sketches for a Mountain-Top Villa\nThe building’s power and the breath of the ridgeline are aligned. The interplay of stone, light, and clouds is handled with great restraint, like a reflection the architect jotted down late at night: how to truly blend the building into the landscape.\n把建筑的力量和山脊的呼吸放在同一条线上。石、光、云的关系被处理得很克制，像设计师深夜记录的一段思考：如何让建筑真正融进风景。\n\nGPT- image 2 prompt👇\nCreate a premium architectural narrative presentation board for a mountaintop villa concept evolution, “Summit Scroll Narrative” edition, designed as a modern architectural scroll-like composition rather than a rigid conventional grid. The board must still preserve a clear three-part hierarchy, but the visual reading rhythm should feel like an elegant unfolding story: a dominant final design hero image at the top, a flowing sequence of conceptual hand-drawn studies and pale watercolor ideation in the middle, and a poetic atmospheric imagery zone at the bottom that acts as the emotional conclusion of the project.\n\nTop hero image:\nA breathtaking final rendering of a contemporary mountaintop villa dramatically positioned along a ridge or cliff edge, fully resolved and architecturally believable. The villa should feel gravity-defying yet serene: long cantilevered slabs, thin roof planes, floor-to-ceiling glazing, stone retaining walls, warm interior light, floating terraces, and panoramic views across misty mountain layers. The hero image must be cinematic, realistic, and highly premium, showing the final design as the culmination of the entire conceptual journey. The architecture should dominate visually but remain elegant and quiet rather than aggressive.\n\nMiddle narrative sequence:\nBelow the hero image, arrange a sequence of smaller concept panels as if the design is being gradually unrolled in front of the viewer. These panels should not feel like a stiff box grid; instead, they should feel rhythmically paced, with varied widths, slight shifts in alignment, and carefully controlled breathing space, like a contemporary design scroll. Show black-and-white hand-drawn massing studies, line-perspective sketches, section fragments, terrain response diagrams, detached cantilever tests, circulation ideas, elevation rhythm studies, and pale watercolor concept overlays. The studies should feel highly refined and deliberate, like the notebook pages of a world-class architect. The linework must be crisp, elegant, and premium, with restrained pale washes in warm gray, light stone beige, muted moss, smoke green, and faint ink-black diffusion. These are concept explorations, not formal polished renderings.\n\nBottom emotional imagery zone:\nAt the bottom, place one wider poetic atmosphere image or a pair of linked mood fragments that express the soul of the project. This zone should feel less analytical and more meditative: perhaps a solitary figure on a mountain edge, the villa glowing in the distance at dusk, wind moving through grasses, mist filling the valley, and a sense of retreat, silence, altitude, and emotional architecture. This section should feel like the final breath of the board, the place where the concept becomes mythic and human.\n\nOverall composition logic:\nThe full board should read vertically but also feel like a soft visual journey from vision to ideation to spirit. Avoid making every module identical. Let the composition resemble a curated architectural exhibition panel or a contemporary scroll of design thinking. Use strong hierarchy, elegant alignment, generous negative space, and visual pacing so that the board feels highly designed and editorial rather than merely technical.\n\nArchitectural identity:\nThe villa language should merge modern luxury retreat architecture with mountain sensitivity: concrete slabs, charcoal stone, pale plaster, smoked wood, warm oak interiors, slim black steel frames, open terraces, terrain-integrated platforms, and quiet landscape insertions. The design should feel exclusive, buildable, contemplative, and world-class.\n\nTypography and layout:\nUse a Chinese main title such as “山顶别墅概念推演设计” paired with an English subtitle such as “SUMMIT VILLA NARRATIVE STUDY” or “MOUNTAINTOP VILLA CONCEPT EVOLUTION”. Typography should be integrated like a premium architectural exhibition board, not a commercial poster. Add refined English annotation lines, numbered concept notes, section labels, terrain comments, and a few short editorial architectural phrases. The title area should feel elegant and intentional, while the smaller text should help guide the narrative flow through the scroll-like sequence. Keep all fonts thin, precise, spacious, and beautiful. No crude bold type, no messy infographic density.\n\nColor palette:\nUse a premium restrained palette: charcoal black, graphite gray, ivory paper, soft stone beige, muted forest green, pale mist gray, warm amber interior light, and subtle ink-wash accents. The final hero image should be richer and more realistic, while the concept panels remain mostly monochrome with delicate pale watercolor touches. The bottom mood zone should feel atmospheric and cinematic but still harmonize with the rest of the board.\n\nLighting and rendering:\nThe hero image must have refined cinematic architectural lighting and realistic mountain atmosphere. The concept sketches should feel crisp, clean, paper-based, and intelligently hand-rendered. The bottom mood imagery should feel poetic, spacious, and gently luminous. The whole board must look like a premium architectural publication spread fused with a design competition presentation sheet.\n\nMood:\nelevated, visionary, poetic, architectural, narrative, premium, serene, intelligent, editorial, contemplative.\n\nRendering style:\nhyper-realistic final architectural visualization combined with refined black-and-white hand-drawn concept studies, pale watercolor architectural ideation, premium editorial scroll-like board composition, museum-grade presentation design, 8k, sharp but elegant.\n\nNegative prompt:\ncheap infographic board, childish sketches, messy watercolor, rigid repetitive grid, cartoon house, cluttered layout, oversaturated colors, generic villa render, ugly bold fonts, low-detail terrain, chaotic notes, sci-fi architecture, random disconnected concept panels",
      "prompt_ko": "@ou_zhen599 산정상 빌라 컨셉 진화 프레젠테이션 보드 \"Summit Scroll Narrative\" — 경직된 그리드 대신 우아하게 펼쳐지는 스크롤 서사. 상단=능선/절벽의 최종 히어로 렌더(완결·설득력), 중단=손그림 컨셉 스터디+옅은 수채 아이데이션 흐름, 하단=시적 분위기 이미지(감정적 결말). 석·빛·구름의 절제된 관계. [xxd 건축보드 계열의 베리에이션]. 3:4.",
      "gen_prompt": "A premium architectural narrative presentation board for a mountaintop villa concept evolution, 'Summit Scroll' edition, composed as an elegant vertical unfolding story rather than a rigid conventional grid, 3:4. It preserves a clear three-part hierarchy. Top: a breathtaking final hero rendering of a contemporary mountaintop villa dramatically positioned along a cliff ridge, glass volumes and natural stone, fully resolved and architecturally believable. Middle: a flowing sequence of conceptual hand-drawn studies, section sketches and pale watercolor ideation showing the design evolution. Bottom: a poetic atmospheric imagery zone — layered ridgelines, drifting clouds and soft light — acting as the emotional conclusion. Restrained interplay of stone, light and clouds, fine annotation text, thin leader lines, muted earthy palette, refined architectural editorial layout, generous negative space, high-end concept board aesthetic.",
