      "title": "아르데코 흑백 미니어처 극장 도시 포스터 2x2 (히든젬 도시 → 무대화된 유물, op-art 모션+전시 라벨, black/ivory/silver)",
      "prompt": "I asked GPT to show me 4 hidden gem cities around the world. 2x2 grid, 16:9, do this for 4 lesser known hidden gem cities: INPUT = $SUBJECT. 1. Convert subject into an iconic theatrical emblem (identity, iconic silhouette, signature landmark forms, symbolic props, flow/energy). 2. Build Art Deco poster architecture: stepped arches, sunburst rays, vertical tower ribs, ornamental corners, bold title plaque, circular medallions; palette black, ivory white, silver gray; thick outer borders, crisp internal stripes. 3. Build a physical miniature relief inside the poster from matte ivory paper, black cut card, painted gray resin, shallow plaster relief, tiny paper architecture; low physical relief with visible layer shadows; front-facing theatrical poster stage. 4. Remap subject details into Deco systems: tiny landmarks, window grids, gear motifs, parallel stripe fields, symbol medallions, architectural silhouettes, small exhibit props. 5. Add controlled motion as graphic pattern: op-art waves, curving speed bands, radiating sunbursts, diagonal beams, smoke-like line ribbons; black, white and silver only. 6. Add Art Deco marquee title, small exhibit plaque, minimal caption strip, decorative stamp, numbered panel mark. RENDER: luxury monochrome poster-theater; orthographic or slight three-quarter product view; soft gallery light creating tiny relief shadows; paper grain, cut edges, matte plaster, clean ink; elegant, mysterious, cinematic, collectible. AVOID: bright color, manga sketchiness, pastel clay softness, messy tourist collage, photoreal people, modern glossy UI, crowded unreadable typography.",
      "prompt_ko": "임의 주제($SUBJECT, 여기선 잘 알려지지 않은 히든젬 도시 4곳)를 흑백 아르데코 미니어처 극장 포스터 2x2 16:9로 만드는 @Gdgtify 함수형(파이썬 의사코드) 템플릿. 도시를 아이코닉 실루엣 엠블럼으로 변환 → 아르데코 프레임(스텝아치·선버스트·타워리브·장식코너·타이틀플라크·원형 메달리온, black/ivory/silver, 두꺼운 외곽선+샤프 내부 스트라이프) → 매트 아이보리지·흑색 컷카드·회색 레진·종이 건축의 얕은 물리 릴리프 극장 → 디테일을 데코 시스템(미니 랜드마크·창격자·기어모티프·스트라이프·메달리온)으로 리맵 → op-art 모션(스피드밴드·선버스트·다이애거널빔, 흑백은/실버만) → 아르데코 마퀴 타이포+전시 플라크+넘버 패널. 럭셔리 모노크롬 포스터시어터. gen_prompt=발파라이소/헨트/가나자와/트빌리시 4도시 구체화.",
      "gen_prompt": "A 2x2 grid, 16:9, of four lesser-known hidden-gem cities, each rendered as a black-and-white Art Deco miniature theater poster: top-left Valparaiso, Chile with its funicular hills and colorful-but-monochrome tiered houses; top-right Ghent, Belgium with medieval guild towers and canal; bottom-left Kanazawa, Japan with its castle gate and garden lantern; bottom-right Tbilisi, Georgia with sulfur-bath domes and cliffside balconies. Each panel: the city's iconic silhouette becomes a staged relic inside an Art Deco frame of stepped arches, sunburst rays, vertical tower ribs, ornamental corners, a bold title plaque and circular medallions; palette strictly black, ivory white and silver gray, thick outer borders and crisp internal stripes. A shallow physical relief theater built from matte ivory paper, black cut card, painted gray resin and tiny paper architecture with visible layer shadows. Op-art motion fields - curving speed bands, radiating sunbursts, diagonal beams - in black, white and silver only. Art Deco marquee title typography with a small exhibit plaque and a numbered panel mark per city. Elegant, mysterious, cinematic, collectible luxury monochrome poster-theater; soft gallery light, paper grain, clean ink. No bright color, no clay softness, no photoreal people, no crowded tourist collage.",
